 RULE TYPE         │ DETAILS                                                                        
───────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 Name              │ secret_push_protection                                                         
───────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 ID                │ 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001                                           
───────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 Applicable Entity │ repository                                                                     
───────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 Release phase     │ beta                                                                           
───────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 Description       │ Verifies that secret push protection is enabled for a given repository. Note   
                   │ that this will will not work as expected for private repositories unless you   
                   │ have GitHub Advanced Security enabled. If you still want to use this rule      
                   │ because you have a mixture of private and public repositories, enable the      
                   │ `skip_private_repos` flag.                                                     
───────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 Ingest type       │ rest                                                                           
───────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 Eval type         │ rego                                                                           
───────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 Guidance          │ Ensure that secret scanning push protection is enabled for the repository. You 
                   │ can use secret scanning to prevent supported secrets from being pushed into    
                   │ your repository by enabling secret scanning push protection. For more          
                   │ information, see GitHub's documentation                                        
                   │ https://docs.github.com/en/code-security/secret-                               
                   │ scanning/push-protection-for-repositories-and-                                 
                   │ organizations#enabling-secret-scanning-as-a-push- protection-for-              
                   │ a-repository.                                                                  
───────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 Remediation       │ rest                                                                           
───────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 Alert             │ security_advisory                                                              
